  "body": "We have several APIs for selecting a peer when we want to fetch data: `LightPeerChain.get_best_peer()`, `PeerPool.get_random_peer()`, `PeerPool.peers`, `StateDownloader.get_idle_peer()` and a couple places in `FastChainSyncer` that sort/filter `PeerPool.peers` based on some criteria. \r\n\r\nApart from `StateDownloader.get_idle_peer()`, I think we should be able to have a single API on `PeerPool` that returns a peer known to have a certain block (defined by its number or TD). That would avoid duplication and ensure we always request data to peers known to have them.",
